glosses: to stack, pile (arms); to prop (poles, etc.) together
to put up (a framework of poles or timbers)
to tie on (a cloth worn around the forehead)
to meet with, come up against, run up against (someone or something unpleasant)

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish چاتمق (çatmak, “to bring together”), from Proto-Turkic *čat- (“to bring together”). Cognate with Karakhanid جَتْماقْ (čatmāq).
